    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - IC BUS SERVICE MANUAL - WINDOWS - SIDE WINDOW - GLASS
        REPLACEMENT PROCEDURE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="6">
        <title>SIDE WINDOW - GLASS REPLACEMENT PROCEDURE</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>- Always wear safety glasses and gloves to prevent accidents from occurring. Extreme care should
                    always be taken when handling glass and repair tools.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove each fastener that secures the window in position. Use a large-tip crosshead
                screwdriver (see
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700167">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt the top of the window out and away from the dome light panel (light bar). See
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700168">Figure 62</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the window frame up and out of the window opening. Pushout side windows equipped with
                buzzer wires will have wires routed from the window latch to the window header. Inspect the wire
                routing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To replace the upper glass, lower glass or window latches, remove the window channel
                fasteners on each side of the window frame with a #15 torque screw. The window channel secures the
                latch, upper and lower glass in the window frame.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>A #15 size torque screw is required to remove the window frame fasteners (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f4700169">Figure 63)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the window frame and the window seal. If the glass is cracked or broken, use extreme
                care.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install replacement glass with the ASA sticker in a readable position, while inserting the
                glass in the window frame.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Re-install sealer to the outside of the window frame.</para>
        </step1>
